The paper proposes a framework for suture thread detection in robotic surgery using deep learning. This involves image analysis and computer vision techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The use of deep learning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of medical imaging, which could potentially fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
